com.complexible.common.io

Class OutputStreamDataOutput

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.io.OutputStream
      • com.complexible.common.io.OutputStreamDataOutput
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, DataOutput, Flushable, AutoCloseable

    public class OutputStreamDataOutput
extends OutputStream
implements DataOutput

    A DataOutput as an OutputStream, akin to DataOutputStream in that both classes are a DataOutput and an OutputStream, so rather than declaring a parameter is type DataOutputStream you can revert to using <T extends OutputStream & DataOutput> and be able to use either class. Unlike DataOutputStream, this class assumes you have a DataOutput to start with rather than an OutputStream.

    Since:
    1.0
